$KTOV -  I've had a hard time connecting the dots between Boxer Capital (BCTG's sponsor) and $LLY .   Looking back at the best link between Boxer Capital and Lilly which is - Loxo Oncology.  Things start making sense .

In light of @Mattsven update about BCTG and talking with @LIKEABOSS1986 about potentials.  Hear me out.

Boxer Capital purchased a majority position in Loxo Oncology In March of 2018.   Loxo's flagship drug LOXO-305 was nearly ready to start trials.   In December of 2018 Loxo started the first-in-human multi-center phase 1/2 trial of LOXO-305 using 3+3 design (sound familiar). 

In 2019 Boxer sell's their stake in Loxo to $LLY for 8b.  What this potentially means for $KTOV.   Boxer acquires Kitov using BCTG and funds the rest of their trials and positions them to sell to $LLY in the future.  I think history typically repeats itself.  The precedent is there.   Not wishing my life away... but the 13th can't happen soon enough.

Now $LLY is trying to get their own drug approved to make up for the demand of Regeneron

links.title: Eli Lilly requests emergency approval for its Covid-19 antibody treatment
links.description: Drugmaker Eli Lilly said Wednesday that it has requested an emergency use authorization from the Food and Drug Administration for its Covid-19 monoclonal antibody treatment. Lilly's medication is similar to the Regeneron antibody treatment President Donald Trump received after his Covid-19 diagnosis. Regeneron has not yet applied for such an authorization.
